# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# |<----  Using a Maximum Of 120 Characters  ---->|

# Explain why this change is being made
# |<----   Try To Limit Each Line to a Maximum Of 120 Characters   ---->|

# Provide links or keys to any relevant tickets, articles or other resources
# Example: Closes #23

# --- COMMIT END ---
# Type can be:
#    feat     (new feature)
#    fix      (bug fix)
#    docs     (documentation)
#    style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc)
#    refactor (refactoring code)
#    test     (adding missing tests)
#    chore    (maintenance, deps)
#    perf     (performance improvement)
#    ci       (CI/CD changes)
#    build    (build system changes)
#    revert   (revert previous commit)
# --------------------
# Scope is REQUIRED. Examples per project type:
#    Generic:  config, deps, docs, ci
#    Backend:  auth, api, db, queue
#    Frontend: ui, components, store
#    CLI:      command, service, helpers
#    Update commitlint.config.mjs with your project scopes.
# --------------------
# Remember to:
#    - Use imperative mood in the subject line
#    - Do not end the subject line with a period
#    - Separate subject from body with a blank line
#    - Use the body to explain what and why vs. how
# --------------------
